Task Management API – ASP.NET Core

REST API built with ASP.NET Core following Clean Architecture principles.
The project models business rules inside the Domain layer and separates responsibilities across API, Application, Infrastructure, and Domain.



----Technologies

-ASP.NET Core Web API

-C#

-Entity Framework Core

-SQL Server

-Clean Architecture

-FluentValidation

-xUnit + Moq (Unit Testing)

|------------Prerequisites-------|

.NET 8.0 SDK 

SQL Server

|----------- Architecture ----------------|

The solution is structured into four layers:

-Domain → Entities, business rules, exceptions

-Application → UseCases, DTOs, validation

-Infrastructure → EF Core, repositories, SQL Server

-API → Controllers, middleware, Swagger

This separation ensures maintainability, testability, and scalability.


|-------- Business Rules-------------------|

Tasks follow a strict lifecycle:

-Pending

-InProgress

-Completed

-Blocked

Rules enforced in the Domain:

A task can only start if it is Pending.

A task can only complete if it is InProgress.

Invalid transitions throw domain exceptions.

|--------- Features------------|
Commands

-Create Task

-Start Task

-Complete Task

-Block / Unblock Task

-Queries

-Get Task by Id

-Get Tasks by State

-Get All Tasks (optional filters)

-Get Tasks with Pagination

|----------Filtering & Pagination--------|

Optional filters:

-GET /api/task?state=InProgress&title=api


Pagination (database-level using Skip/Take):

-GET /api/task/paged?pageNumber=1&pageSize=10


Efficient queries are executed directly in SQL Server.

|-------Validation--------|

Validation handled in Application layer using FluentValidation:

Title required (max 200 characters)

Description max 1000 characters

PageNumber > 0

PageSize within allowed limits

|----------Exception Handling--------|

Global middleware maps exceptions to proper HTTP status codes:

-400 → Invalid input

-404 → Not found

-409 → Business rule violation

-500 → Unexpected error

|--------------Testing----------|

-Unit tests implemented using xUnit and Moq.

-Domain Tests

-State transitions (Start, Complete, Block, Unblock)

-Business rule validation

-Application Tests

-UseCase behavior

-DTO mapping

-Pagination calculation

-Validator behavior

|-----------Running the Project--------|

Configure connection string in appsettings.json

-Run migrations:

-dotnet ef database update

-Start the API:

-dotnet run


Access Swagger:

https://localhost:{port}/swagger
